 mod-vhost-ldap-ng is Apache 2.x module for storing and configuring
 Virtual Hosts from LDAP.  It supports DocumentRoot, ScriptAlias,
 ServerName, ServerAlias, ServerAdmin and SuexecUserGroup directives.
 
It's build on top of mod_ldap, so it uses it's caching capabilities
 and can be used with threaded apache.

This module is a fork of mod-vhost-ldap (http://modvhostldap.alioth.debian.org/)
to implements new functionalities to make it more flexible for ISP environments.

Ardeek note on mod_vhost_ldap_ng:
mod_ldap dependency is dropped moving to more flexible client library, OpenLDAP.
